If auth test works on GCE only, shall we make the test case generation more intelligent so we can still run the whole testcase file manually from local?

For example, instead of 

docker run --test_case=non-authtest
docker run --test_case=auth-test

Can we do
docker run ... --test_case=non-authtest
test <is_on_gce> && docker run ... --test_case=authtest
?
There's definitely ways to work around this. Same for cloud gateways and gateways. But I'd like to do that in a separate PR, if you don't mind. I added comments.

Supporting "master" is a quick way to verify the sanity of the framework itself without relying on complex "git checkout" logic.  Without it, how do you plan to quickly test changes of the driver?

Also if we add auth tests like this, we lose the ability to run the test case script locally.  Can we at least add an env to skip auth tests during runtime so we can still run the generated test cases with command like 

docker_image=gcr.io/grpc-testing/grpc_interop_go1.7:master **skip_auth=1** ./testcases/go__master

?

When you create new tests, you don't need to change or add new images. Note that I'm not changing the version of the test cases, which is still just "master" right now. I'm just removing "master" images.

If we want to test the framework itself, I think it's better to add a test script. The master images are confusing as we don't know easily which commit it was created from. We probably should cleanup the GCS as well to remove all images that were created for testing the framework and only keep the official ones.
Reverted the change of removing master images. PTAL.
